texts.text: >Along an empty backstreet,
>there lies a secret entrance.
>And beyond that door...
G'day, my dearest Lady Nekomata. Your fur is lovelier than ever!
*Sigh*
It's lunchtime, and look at this fine weather. So, how about it?
Will you...join me for tea?
You ask me out every day. Take a hint already.
I wouldn't date you in a million years. Later.
>Cait Sith's advances are refused...
As usual, you keep me on my toes!
I'm falling for you all over again, Lady Nekomata!
When will you learn no means no, Cait Sith?
*Sigh* As a citizen, I'm ashamed to call you our king.
Hey! You guys were spying?!
I'll admit my advances are pretty lame for a ruler.
Fine, you won't see me like this anymore.
Wow, you finally get it.
Yes, a king should maintain a certain level of decorum—
I mean you won't SEE me get dumped again!
I'll ask Lady Nekomata to tea another time!
Ugh, that's not what I meant!
Cait Sith ain't no quitter. Or maybe he's just a masochist.
That's not how I see it.
Cait Sith's tenacity has molded him into a fine king.
You think? I've only seen him walk around shootin' the breeze.
Master Shionyan is way more regal.
Well to be fair, she's also a cruel sadist to us demon allies.
Nyahaha! So, Cait Sith is less dignified than a human!
Still, I think our king likes his "down-to-earth" image.
"Down to earth," huh?
Yes. Most of our citizens are weak, displaced demons.
To raise their spirits, he walks with them, talks with them,
and goes far beyond the call of duty.
Whoa, really?
You don't live here, so of course you wouldn't know.
Still, I wish Cait Sith would get his act together.
I mean, he IS our king.
Nyahaha! Such grievances are proof of peace.
I feel bliss beyond measure. Cait Sith is a superb king.
>The aforementioned hole-in-the-wall connects to an Aura Gate.
>Here, uprooted demons live together in the Cait Sith Kingdom.
>However...
We meet again, Lady Nekomata!
Just my luck... GIVE. IT. UP!
Perseverance is a virtue!
I'd be honored it if you joined me for tea this aftern—
Ah!
Huh? What's wrong?
What is THAT?
>Cait Sith notices a flood of brilliant light.
>And from within that glow...
So, this is where "he" will supposedly make an appearance.
Get to work.
Sir!
Hey, what's going on?
Divine forces...?
Hey! Who are you people?!
Look, Sir Camael. Demons.
Locals? What a nuisance. We have precious little time as it is.
No matter. I shall explain and promptly bid them leave.
I am Cait Sith the King!
Who are you? Why have you come? Explain yourselves!
I am the Herald Camael. I command the Powers here.
I understand it's short notice, but please leave immediately.
Meow?!
Yo, who do you think you are?!
...And may I ask why?
An otherworldly demon named Rahab will arrive soon.
I sensed this bitter heretic and have orders to vanquish him.
To confront the heinous Rahab, we must be aptly organized.
Therefore, this land shall serve as our frontline.
An otherworldly demon...?
"Frontline" or not, we can't just...
...I understand your dilemma.
However, I can't tell everyone to leave out of the blue.
You're quite relaxed despite the peril knocking at your door.
Maybe, but many demons call this land "home."
Their lives are in my hands...
That's why I can't answer just yet! Please, give me time!
Cait Sith...
...I understand.
Then discussion is futile.
God's command is above all else.
Those who interfere shall face our Divine wrath.
All hands, eliminate every last demon in this land!
Sir!
>On Camael's orders, the angels start to mobilize.
Hey! Don't we get a vote?!
A-Ack! I don't even live here!
We needn't show mercy to demons. Now, be on your way.
Ngh! If that's how it's gonna be...!
Gah!
Cait Sith...
You were holdin' back this whole time?!
Ever since I became king, I've studied the sword daily.
I didn't expect a practical test like this though...
Such actions are a sin against God.
God can bite me! It's my duty to protect this land!
I'll save us from you angels!
...Foolish demon.
Your Majesty! I'll join the fight.
Everyone! Let us gather our kingdom's forces here and meow!
Together with Cait Sith, we'll raise a war cry!
> The crowd of demons voice their ardent resolve.
Everyone... Thank you so much!
Let's fight for our nation!
So be it, witless demon pagans.
May death absolve you!
>As Camael and his angels charge forward,
>Cait Sith's army prepares to defend their kingdom.
C-Crap... It's not like I'd be of much help anyway...
But I like this country. I can't just abandon everyone.
...! Of course! The Liberators can save us!
Hang in there, guys! Help is on the way!
